customrecordcustomfield.help: The NetSuite Customer for this Subscription. This is from the native NetSuite Customer list.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Customer

customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter the Master Contract (if any) for this Subscription. Master Contracts are used mainly in the scenarios in which there is a single contract in place that applies to multiple Subscriptions or Customers (for example, a parent company has a contract which applies to many of its subsidiaries).
customrecordcustomfield.label: Master Contract

customrecordcustomfield.help: This is an optional field that can be used to identify this Subscription from an external source. This may often be a Contract # or External ID associated with a proprietary system.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Identification Number

customrecordcustomfield.help: If you select this option, the Charge Schedule set at the Master Contract level will be used to setup the Charges for this Subscription -- as long as the individual Subscription Item(s) don't have their own independent Charge Schedule selected.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Inherit Charge Schedule From Master Contract

customrecordcustomfield.help: This feature is not currently supported.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Initial Charge Period End Date

customrecordcustomfield.description: Indicates if Invoice is already "Approved" for this Subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Indicates if Invoice is already "Approved" for this Subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Invoice Approved

customrecordcustomfield.description: Indicates if Customer Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) is above $100K.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Indicates if Customer Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) is above $100K.
customrecordcustomfield.label: ARR Amount Check

customrecordcustomfield.help: This is the primary Revenue Order created for this Subscription. This value will automatically be set whenever a new Revenue Order is created for this Subscription and this field is not populated.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Revenue Order

customrecordcustomfield.help: Description of Subscription rejection reason.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Rejection Reason Memo

customrecordcustomfield.help:
Select the Revenue Configuration to be applied to this Subscription if you are using the Revenue Management functionality to integrate with the NetSuite Advanced Revenue Management module. The Revenue Configuration record determines how the individual Charges generated under this Subscription are summarized/aggregated (if at all) when creating the ZAB Revenue Details which eventually become ARM Revenue Elements.
NOTE: If you do not specify a value here the system will not process ZAB Revenue transactions for this Subscription. If you do have a value entered here, any Subscription Items that do not have a Revenue Type specified will be omitted from ZAB Revenue processes.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Revenue Configuration

customrecordcustomfield.help: Select the default Renewal Template to be applied for this Subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Renewal Template

customrecordcustomfield.help: This field stores employee approved this subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.label: First Level Approved By

customrecordcustomfield.help: (this feature is not supported in this version)
customrecordcustomfield.label: Evergreen Period in Months

customrecordcustomfield.help: If this Subscription was created from a Renewal Estimate the originating record will be listed here.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Created From Renewal Estimate

customrecordcustomfield.help: If this Subscription was created from a Renewal Estimate the Primary Subscription will be listed here.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Created From Primary Subscription

customrecordcustomfield.help:
This field will default to the Customer value but can be changed if you would like to record the transactions (bills and revenue transactions) under a different Customer record. The most common example would be used for Consolidated Invoicing options. During “record creation” this field will be the source for other fields on the Subscription -- such as default Currency and Subsidiary.
You can also set individual Bill To Customers at the Subscription Item level if you want to bill multiple entities by line item.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Bill To Customer

customrecordcustomfield.help: This field will always match the Bill To Customer value on this Subscription. The Entity version of the Bill To Customer field is required for filtering on Address Book fields and similar definitions.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Bill To Entity

customrecordcustomfield.description: This field enables when Subscription is created through Data Migration Process
customrecordcustomfield.help: This field enables when Subscription is created through Data Migration Process
customrecordcustomfield.label: Is Data Migrated

customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter the Currency for this Subscription. The Currency must be a supported currency for the Bill To Entity.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Currency

customrecordcustomfield.help: Sourced from the Currency field on this record, the Locale can be used to properly format amount fields based on the Currency in email templates and other reports.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Locale

customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter the Billing Profile to be applied to this Subscription. The Billing Profile will dictate various presentation options for the sales transactions created - such as when to separate transactions, combine Charges into a single line, and sort lines.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Billing Profile

customrecordcustomfield.help: Checking this box will automatically consolidate transactions for the same Bill To Customer when the Bill Date, Currency, Subsidiary, Bill To Address, and Ship To Address (Header) match -- with exceptions if you have a Billing Profile that includes "Separate" fields or you have selected a Consolidation Group on the Subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Consolidate Billing

customrecordcustomfield.help: If you have selected the "Consolidate Billing" option, you can optionally specify an additional Consolidation Group to further refine how transactions are to be grouped together from the consolidated population. In other words, if the transactions have the same Bill To Customer, Currency, Subsidiary, Billing Profile, etc. this Consolidation Group can split the population into multiple groups that you define here.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Consolidation Group (Optional)

customrecordcustomfield.help:
This value indicates which type of Transaction should be generated when Charges for this Subscription are billed. If no value is selected on the Subscription, the default Transaction Type configured in ZAB Preferences will apply unless overridden on the Subscription Item or Billing Profile level.
NOTE: Cash Sales are currently unsupported by ZAB Revenue functionality. Please ensure that Sales Order or Invoice is selected for ZAB Revenue contracts.
customrecordcustomfield.label: [scriptid=custcollectiontranslations_pivot_20_a915caeda51e4f77afacc3c.report_measure_69_3]

customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter the default Payment Terms you would like to use for Transactions created by this Subscription. This is an optional field and if left blank the Payment Terms listed on an associated Billing Profile or the default Payment Terms for the Bill To Entity will be used.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Payment Terms

customrecordcustomfield.help: Any value entered here will post to the PO # field in the header of any billed transaction.
customrecordcustomfield.label: PO / Reference #

customrecordcustomfield.help:
Enter the Subsidiary (if any) that should be associated with this Subscription. The Subsidiary should be compatible with the Customer selected.
A value entered here may prevent certain users from seeing this record if their Role does not give them access to this Subsidiary.
customrecordcustomfield.label: [scriptid=custcollectiontranslations_dataset_29_684eb041b4ad44be95ecc.dataset_field_31_7]

customrecordcustomfield.help:
Enter the Department (if any) that should be associated with this Subscription. This value will default to the header of any transaction created as well as be the default value for any Subscription Items to populate line-level Department fields on transactions.
A value entered here may prevent certain users from seeing this record if their Role does not give them access to this Department.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Department

customrecordcustomfield.help:
Enter the Location (if any) that should be associated with this Subscription. This value will default to the header of any transaction created as well as be the default value for any Subscription Items to populate line-level Location fields on transactions.
A value entered here may prevent certain users from seeing this record if their Role does not give them access to this Location.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Location

customrecordcustomfield.help:
Enter the Class (if any) that should be associated with this Subscription. This value will default to the header of any transaction created as well as be the default value for any Subscription Items to populate line-level Class fields on transactions.
A value entered here may prevent certain users from seeing this record if their Role does not give them access to this Class.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Class

customrecordcustomfield.help: You can optionally select an Alternate Entity to allow sourcing of these additional address book entries into the "Bill To Address" dropdown list. The Bill To Address is typically sourced from the Bill To Entity but if you select an Alternate Entity here you will be able to select from both sets of address books. A common use case might be if you want the Bill To Entity (Customer on the Transaction) to remain the same but the billing address should be from a Partner/Reseller address book.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Bill To Address - Alternate Entity

customrecordcustomfield.help:
You can optionally enter the Billing Address that you would like to use when creating a Transaction. If you do not enter a value here (or on the line level) the default billing address for the Bill To Customer will appear on the transaction.
The list of Billing Addresses available is filtered based on the "Bill To Entity" and "Bill To Address - Alternate Entity" on the Subscription record.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Bill To Address

customrecordcustomfield.help: You can optionally select an Alternate Entity to allow sourcing of these additional address book entries into the "Ship To Address" dropdown list. The Ship To Address is typically sourced from the Bill To Entity but if you select an Alternate Entity here you will be able to select from both sets of address books. A common use case might be if you want the Bill To Entity (Customer on the Transaction) to remain the same but the shipping address should be from an End User address book.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Ship To Address - Alternate Entity

customrecordcustomfield.help:
You can optionally enter the Ship To Address that you would like to use when creating a Transaction. If you do not enter a value here (or on the line level) the default shipping address for the Bill To Customer will appear on the transaction.
The list of Shipping Addresses available is filtered based on the "Bill To Entity" and "Ship To Address - Alternate Entity" on the Subscription record.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Ship To Address

customrecordcustomfield.help: This function will dictate whether the billing transaction will use the Ship To Address at the header or line item level. In order to use this feature you will need to have enabled Multiple Shipping Routes. The following options are available: NEVER: The Ship To Address will always be placed in the header of the billing transaction. In situations where multiple Ship To Addresses are present during processing, the system will automatically split into multiple transactions so only a single Ship To Address is present on each transaction. This option is the default value for this field but can be changed under ZAB Preferences ONLY WHEN NEEDED: The Ship To Address will be placed on the header of the transaction except in cases where multiple Ship To Addresses are present when processing — and in those cases the system will enable line item shipping for that transaction. ALWAYS: Ship To Address(es) will always be placed on the line level even when all lines are the same address.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Enable Line Item Shipping

customrecordcustomfield.help:
The Shipping Method can be selected on the Subscription record and this value will post through to the billing transaction. Depending on whether you have "Enable Line Item Shipping" selected, the results of this field will appear in the header of the transaction or on each line of the transaction.
You can also select a Shipping Method at the Subscription Item level if you need to be more specific as opposed to applying a single method for the entire Subscription.
Please note you will have to ensure the Shipping Method you have selected is compatible with the Subsidiary and Shipping Carrier that will apply to the transaction otherwise an error will be thrown or the field will be null during the Create Transaction process.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Shipping Method

customrecordcustomfield.help: Primary use case would be to store the primary contact(s) of the Customer associated with the Subscription. This is useful for renewals, email notifications, and other subscription management purposes.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Contact(s)

customrecordcustomfield.help: Optionally use this field to record and communicate descriptive information about the Subscription.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Notes

customrecordcustomfield.help: If 'ZAB Payment ID Generation Type' is set to 'Subscription Payment ID' in ZAB Preferences, the ZP Payment Group ID will be auto-generated upon creation of the Subscription. If 'ZAB Payment ID Generation Type' is 'None', an ID will not be generated and must be manually entered.
customrecordcustomfield.label: ZP Payment Group ID

customrecordcustomfield.description: This fields will hold the terminated contract ID.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Terminated contract

customrecordcustomfield.help: This ID field is available to display the hyperlink of Subscription present in Salesforce.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Salesforce Link

customrecordcustomfield.help: This ID field is available for integrations to Salesforce to represent the unique ID.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Salesforce ID

customrecordcustomfield.description: Error text when this Subscription and its related Subscription Charges are being processed for a Transaction and an error occurs.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Error text when this Subscription and its related Subscription Charges are being processed for a Transaction and an error occurs.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Processing Error
